Description: Convert BBS ANSI files to other formats
 This Python package provides an abstract, extensible mechanism to
 parse, render and save text files with terminal directives.
 .
 In its present state, it can be used to render 'ANSI' files from the
 BBS era ('ANSI' referring to the MS-DOS driver ANSI.SYS that
 implemented a subset of the ANSI X.364 terminal directives).
 .
 More input and output formats may be easily implemented on top of the
 defined Python classes.
